description.narrative: In 2021, the;Covid-19 pandemic presented major challenge to keep children in school and learning. In this context, UNICEF supported MINEDH with the development and dissemination of an;Operational Plan;for the;Violence against Children referral and reporting mechanism;and with the development of a;life skills manual;for teachers. As part of the back-to-school campaign after schools reopened, UNICEF supported MINEDH in disseminating a;training guide for school councils;on the cross-cutting issues affecting whether children to go and stay in school. Furthermore, the;Inclusive Education Strategy;which focuses particularly on children with disabilities, was successfully launched this year.;; | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/01/2022
